					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12865742#post-4451966</guid>
				<title>Site Criticism Team - Review</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12865742/scp-4981#post-4451966</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 22 Dec 2019 12:29:47 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RockTeethMothEyes</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4022320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Since the above comments don't really offer much in addressing the piece, I'd like to offer a review.</p> <p>That's not to say that I didn't enjoy it. I'm really quite moo-ved myself.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+[Critique]&nbsp;Click&nbsp;to&nbsp;Access</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-[Click&nbsp;to&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;Text]</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>I remember being a bit confused when you showed me this in a draft and the following conversation that occurred in IRC made it a bit clearer what was going on, but it wasn't coming clearly in the article itself. Coming back to it now, I feel that it is <em>very</em> clear what is going on: the cows are easily won over with special treats. The addition of references to cartoonish representations of adoration does so nicely here, giving it a pleasant feeling of &quot;getting it&quot; while showing off such actions in a manner that could be considered gross if you saw it in person.</p> <p>I think the inclusion of the Valentine's Day cards is a bit much, personally. While it does get the point across a bit firmer, it seems like it is almost <em>too</em> forward. It's not an addition I would have put in myself, but I can see why you would include it. That, however, is a small detail that I can overlook. I thoroughly enjoyed the weirdness of this piece, and feel it has earned one uplike.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p><span style="font-size:smaller;"><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> <em>Opinions expressed in this review do not reflect the opinions of SCP Wiki staff as a whole. Please respond to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rockteethmotheyes" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4022320&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1577017787" alt="RockTeethMothEyes" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4022320)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rockteethmotheyes" >RockTeethMothEyes</a></span> or contact the captain of the Site Criticism Team, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=637830&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1577017787" alt="SoullessSingularity" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=637830)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" >SoullessSingularity</a></span>, for any questions or concerns relating to this review.</em></span></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
